<main>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-emerald-500/30">
    <div
      class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-6xl flex-col items-center px-4 py-16 text-center sm:px-6 sm:py-20 lg:px-8 lg:py-24"
    >
      <p
        class="rounded border border-emerald-500/70 px-4 py-1 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-emerald-400 sm:text-xs"
      >
        No one sees what you do here
      </p>
      <h1
        class="mt-8 max-w-4xl text-4xl font-black uppercase leading-tight text-emerald-400 sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl"
      >
        Privacy With Encrypted Chats
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-base text-zinc-300 sm:text-lg">
        Immediate peer-to-peer encryption. No email, no phone number, no
        centralized database. Just a direct, ephemeral link between
        participants.
      </p>

      <div
        id="join-room"
        class="mt-10 flex w-full max-w-xl flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:justify-center"
      >
        <a
          href="#"
          class="inline-flex flex-1 items-center justify-center rounded-none bg-emerald-400 px-6 py-4 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-black transition hover:bg-emerald-300"
        >
          Create A Private Room
        </a>
        <a
          href="#"
          class="inline-flex flex-1 items-center justify-center rounded-none bg-red-500 px-6 py-4 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-white transition hover:bg-red-400"
        >
          Join A Private Room
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section
    id="features"
    class="mx-auto grid w-full max-w-6xl gap-4 px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:grid-cols-3 lg:px-8"
  >
    <article
      class="border border-emerald-500/60 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6 lg:col-span-2"
    >
      <h2
        class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-emerald-400"
      >
        Don't worry about chats, it's encrypted
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-300">
        Communication bypasses our servers. We never see your messages because
        we physically cannot. Your browser is the terminal.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex gap-3">
        <span class="h-5 w-5 border border-zinc-500 bg-zinc-700/50"></span>
        <span class="h-5 w-5 border border-zinc-500 bg-zinc-700/50"></span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6">
      <p class="text-3xl text-emerald-400">⌁</p>
      <h3 class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold uppercase text-zinc-100">
        Temporary Identity
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-300">
        No accounts. No passwords to leak. Your identity is a temporary session
        hash that dissolves when you close the tab.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article id="security" class="border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold uppercase text-zinc-100">
        Secure Connections
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-300">
        We hash room identifiers to generate unique keys for each private room
        and protect the exchange with modern browser cryptography.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6">
      <div
        class="mb-4 border border-emerald-500/40 bg-emerald-950/40 px-4 py-6 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-emerald-300"
      >
        &gt; latency_0.02ms
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold uppercase text-zinc-100">
        Instant Messages
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-300">
        We use sockets and pub/sub style delivery so encrypted messages reach
        participants in real time with low latency.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="border border-emerald-500/60 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold uppercase text-emerald-400">
        Auto-Wipe
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-100">
        All room history is stored in RAM only. Closing the session triggers
        immediate cryptographic shredding of transient data.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</main>
